## Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

### What is a commercial loan used for?

A commercial loan is any business-purpose financing. Common uses include buying equipment, expanding premises, purchasing inventory, covering operational expenses, or financing vehicles. Unlike personal loans, commercial loans are evaluated based on your business's ability to repay.

### How much commercial loan can I get in Malaysia?

The amount depends on several factors: your monthly business turnover, existing debts, the purpose of the loan, and available collateral. For equipment financing, we typically finance the full purchase price of the asset. For working capital, amounts are usually based on your average monthly revenue.

### What documents do I need for a commercial loan?

Standard requirements include SSM company documents, director IC copies, 6 months of business bank statements, and latest financial accounts. For equipment financing, you'll also need the quotation or invoice for what you're purchasing.

### Can I get a commercial loan with bad credit?

It's harder with banks, but not impossible with private financiers. We look at the full picture—your current business health, cash flow, and the purpose of the loan—not just your credit score. If you have a solid business case, we can often find a way to help.

### How long does commercial loan approval take?

Banks typically take 4-8 weeks. At Ing Heng Credit, we aim to give you an answer much faster. The timeline depends on how quickly you can provide complete documentation and the complexity of your case.

